This paper deals with deep generative models and their inference, which are topics commonly studied in the machine learning community. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the biological plausibility of the proposed method, which suggests a connection to the field of computational neuroscience, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another likely category. The paper also mentions auto-encoders and consistency between different groups of inputs, which are topics commonly studied in the fields of computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the use of recurrent neural networks, which are commonly used in control systems (cs.SY).
